zyxelMstp.name: zyxelMstp
zyxelMstp.description: The subtree for Multiple Spanning Tree Protocol (MSTP)

MstiOrCistInstanceIndex.name: MstiOrCistInstanceIndex
MstiOrCistInstanceIndex.description: This textual convention is an extension of the MstiInstanceIndex convention. This extension permits the additional value of zero, which means Common and Internal Spanning Tree (CIST).

zyMstpGeneralConfigIdName.name: zyMstpGeneralConfigIdName
zyMstpGeneralConfigIdName.description: The configuration name that identifies the MST region and is used as one of the inputs in the computation of the MST Configuration Identifier.

zyMstpGeneralConfigIdRevisionLevel.name: zyMstpGeneralConfigIdRevisionLevel
zyMstpGeneralConfigIdRevisionLevel.description: This object identifies the MST revision that identifies the MST region and is used as one of the inputs in the computation of the MST configuration Identifier.

zyMstpGeneralHelloTime.name: zyMstpGeneralHelloTime
zyMstpGeneralHelloTime.description: The time interval in seconds between BPDU configuration message generations by the root switch. The allowed range is 1 to 10 seconds.

zyMstpGeneralMaxAge.name: zyMstpGeneralMaxAge
zyMstpGeneralMaxAge.description: This is the maximum time (in seconds) the switch can wait without receiving a BPDU before attempting to reconfigure

zyMstpGeneralForwardDelay.name: zyMstpGeneralForwardDelay
zyMstpGeneralForwardDelay.description: This is the maximum time (in seconds) the switch will wait before changing states. This delay is required because every switch must receive information about topology changes before it starts to forward frames.

zyMstpGeneralMaxHops.name: zyMstpGeneralMaxHops
zyMstpGeneralMaxHops.description: The number of hops (between 1 and 255) in an MSTP region before the BPDU is discarded and the port information is aged.

zyMstpVlanMapMaxNumberOfInstances.name: zyMstpVlanMapMaxNumberOfInstances
zyMstpVlanMapMaxNumberOfInstances.description: The maximum number of MSTP VLAN instances that can be created.

zyxelMstpVlanMapTable.name: zyxelMstpVlanMapTable
zyxelMstpVlanMapTable.description: The table contains MSTP VLAN map configuration.

zyxelMstpVlanMapEntry.name: zyxelMstpVlanMapEntry
zyxelMstpVlanMapEntry.description: An entry contains MSTP VLAN map configuration.

zyMstpVlanMapInstance.name: zyMstpVlanMapInstance
zyMstpVlanMapInstance.description: Uniquely identifies an instance. The entry of this table with index 0 presents always, represents CIST. When SET operation

zyMstpVlanMapVlans1k.name: zyMstpVlanMapVlans1k
zyMstpVlanMapVlans1k.description: A string of octets containing one bit per VLAN. The first octet corresponds to VLANs with VlanIndex values 1 through 8; the second octet to VLANs 9 through 16 etc. The most significant bit of each octet corresponds to the lowest VlanIndex value in that octet. For each VLAN that is mapped to this MSTP instance, the bit corresponding to that VLAN is set to '1'. Empty (zero) most significant octes are not mandatory.

zyMstpVlanMapVlans2k.name: zyMstpVlanMapVlans2k
zyMstpVlanMapVlans2k.description: A string of octets containing one bit per VLAN for VLANS with VlanIndex values 1024 through 2047. The first octet corresponds to VLANs with VlanIndex values 1024 through 1031; the second octet to VLANs 1032 through 1039 etc. The most significant bit of each octet corresponds to the lowest VlanIndex value in that octet. For each VLAN that is mapped to this MSTP instance, the bit corresponding to that VLAN is set to '1'. Empty (zero) most significant octes are not mandatory.

zyMstpVlanMapVlans3k.name: zyMstpVlanMapVlans3k
zyMstpVlanMapVlans3k.description: A string of octets containing one bit per VLAN for VLANS with VlanIndex values 2048 through 3071. The first octet corresponds to VLANs with VlanIndex values of 2048 through 2055; the second octet to VLANs 2056 through 2063 etc. The most significant bit of each octet corresponds to the lowest VlanIndex value in that octet. For each VLAN that is mapped to this MSTP instance, the bit corresponding to that VLAN is set to '1'. Empty (zero) most significant octes are not mandatory.

zyMstpVlanMapVlans4k.name: zyMstpVlanMapVlans4k
zyMstpVlanMapVlans4k.description: A string of octets containing one bit per VLAN for VLANS with VlanIndex values 3072 through 4095. The first octet corresponds to VLANs with VlanIndex values 3072 through 3079; the second octet to VLANs 3080 through 3087 etc. The most significant bit of each octet corresponds to the lowest VlanIndex value in that octet. For each VLAN that is mapped to this MSTP instance, the bit corresponding to that VLAN is set to '1'. Empty (zero) most significant octes are not mandatory.

zyMstpVlanMapRowStatus.name: zyMstpVlanMapRowStatus
zyMstpVlanMapRowStatus.description: This object allow entries to be created and deleted from the MSTP VLAN map table.

zyxelMstpPortTable.name: zyxelMstpPortTable
zyxelMstpPortTable.description: The table contains MSTP port configuration.

zyxelMstpPortEntry.name: zyxelMstpPortEntry
zyxelMstpPortEntry.description: An entry contains MSTP port configuration.

zyMstpPortAdminEdgePort.name: zyMstpPortAdminEdgePort
zyMstpPortAdminEdgePort.description: The administrative value of the Edge Port parameter. A value of true(1) indicates that this port should be assumed as an edge-port, and a value of false(2) indicates that this port should be assumed as a non-edge-port.

zyxelMstpInstanceTable.name: zyxelMstpInstanceTable
zyxelMstpInstanceTable.description: The table contains MSTP instance configuration.

zyxelMstpInstanceEntry.name: zyxelMstpInstanceEntry
zyxelMstpInstanceEntry.description: An entry contains MSTP instance configuration.

zyMstpInstanceId.name: zyMstpInstanceId
zyMstpInstanceId.description: The number you want to use to identify this MST instance on the switch. 0 means CIST.

zyMstpInstanceBridgePriority.name: zyMstpInstanceBridgePriority
zyMstpInstanceBridgePriority.description: priority of the switch for the specific spanning tree instance. The lower the number , the more likely the switch will be chosen as the root bridge within the spanning tree instance. In steps of 4096.

zyxelMstpInstancePortTable.name: zyxelMstpInstancePortTable
zyxelMstpInstancePortTable.description: The table contains MSTP instance port configuration.

zyxelMstpInstancePortEntry.name: zyxelMstpInstancePortEntry
zyxelMstpInstancePortEntry.description: An entry contains MSTP instance port configuration.

zyMstpInstancePortInstanceId.name: zyMstpInstancePortInstanceId
zyMstpInstancePortInstanceId.description: The number you want to use to identify this MST instance on the switch. 0 means CIST.

zyMstpInstancePortState.name: zyMstpInstancePortState
zyMstpInstancePortState.description: Enable/Disable this port to the MST instance.

zyMstpInstancePortPriority.name: zyMstpInstancePortPriority
zyMstpInstancePortPriority.description: Port priority. Priority decides which port should be disable when more than one port forms a loop in a switch. Ports with a higher priority numeric value are disabled first. In steps of 16.

zyMstpInstancePortPathCost.name: zyMstpInstancePortPathCost
zyMstpInstancePortPathCost.description: The cost of transmitting a frame on to a LAN through that port.

zyMstpInfoGeneralConfigIdName.name: zyMstpInfoGeneralConfigIdName
zyMstpInfoGeneralConfigIdName.description: The configuration name that identifies the MST region and is used as one of the inputs in the computation of the MST Configuration Identifier.

zyMstpInfoGeneralConfigIdRevisionLevel.name: zyMstpInfoGeneralConfigIdRevisionLevel
zyMstpInfoGeneralConfigIdRevisionLevel.description: This object identifies the MST revision that identifies the MST region and is used as one of the inputs in the computation of the MST configuration Identifier.

zyMstpInfoGeneralConfigIdConfigDigest.name: zyMstpInfoGeneralConfigIdConfigDigest
zyMstpInfoGeneralConfigIdConfigDigest.description: A configuration digest is generated from the VLAN-MSTI mapping information. This field displays the 16-octet signature that is included in an MSTP BPDU. This field displays the digest when MSTP is activated on the system.

zyMstpInfoGeneralHelloTime.name: zyMstpInfoGeneralHelloTime
zyMstpInfoGeneralHelloTime.description: The time interval in seconds between BPDU configuration message generations by the root switch.

zyMstpInfoGeneralMaxAge.name: zyMstpInfoGeneralMaxAge
zyMstpInfoGeneralMaxAge.description: This is the maximum time (in seconds) the switch can wait without receiving a BPDU before attempting to reconfigure

zyMstpInfoGeneralForwardDelay.name: zyMstpInfoGeneralForwardDelay
zyMstpInfoGeneralForwardDelay.description: This is the maximum time (in seconds) the switch will wait before changing states. This delay is required because every switch must receive information about topology changes before it starts to forward frames.

zyMstpInfoGeneralCistRootPathCost.name: zyMstpInfoGeneralCistRootPathCost
zyMstpInfoGeneralCistRootPathCost.description: This is the path cost from the root port on this switch to the root switch.

zyMstpInfoGeneralCistRootBridgeId.name: zyMstpInfoGeneralCistRootBridgeId
zyMstpInfoGeneralCistRootBridgeId.description: This is the path cost from the root port on this switch to the root switch.

zyxelMstpInfoVlanMapTable.name: zyxelMstpInfoVlanMapTable
zyxelMstpInfoVlanMapTable.description: The table contains MSTP VLAN map information.

zyxelMstpInfoVlanMapEntry.name: zyxelMstpInfoVlanMapEntry
zyxelMstpInfoVlanMapEntry.description: An entry contains MSTP VLAN map information.

zyMstpInfoVlanMapVid.name: zyMstpInfoVlanMapVid
zyMstpInfoVlanMapVid.description: The VLAN ID for which this entry contains the instance mapped.

zyMstpInfoVlanMapInstance.name: zyMstpInfoVlanMapInstance
zyMstpInfoVlanMapInstance.description: An integer with values ranging from 0 to 64 that identify a the CIST/MSTI instance to which this VLAN is mapped

zyxelMstpInfoPortTable.name: zyxelMstpInfoPortTable
zyxelMstpInfoPortTable.description: The table contains MSTP VLAN map information.

zyxelMstpInfoPortEntry.name: zyxelMstpInfoPortEntry
zyxelMstpInfoPortEntry.description: An entry contains MSTP VLAN map information.

zyMstpInfoPortOperEdgePort.name: zyMstpInfoPortOperEdgePort
zyMstpInfoPortOperEdgePort.description: The operational value of the Edge Port parameter. The object is initialized to the value of the corresponding instance of zyxelMstpPortAdminEdgePort. When the corresponding instance of zyxelMstpPortAdminEdgePort is set, this object will be changed as well. This object will also be changed to false on reception of a BPDU.

zyMstpInfoPortOperPointToPointMAC.name: zyMstpInfoPortOperPointToPointMAC
zyMstpInfoPortOperPointToPointMAC.description: The port is operationally connected to a point-to-point link.

zyxelMstpInfoInstanceTable.name: zyxelMstpInfoInstanceTable
zyxelMstpInfoInstanceTable.description: The table contains MSTP instance information.

zyxelMstpInfoInstanceEntry.name: zyxelMstpInfoInstanceEntry
zyxelMstpInfoInstanceEntry.description: An entry contains MSTP instance information.

zyMstpInfoInstanceId.name: zyMstpInfoInstanceId
zyMstpInfoInstanceId.description: the number you want to use to identify this MST instance on the switch. 0 means CIST.

zyMstpInfoInstanceBridgeId.name: zyMstpInfoInstanceBridgeId
zyMstpInfoInstanceBridgeId.description: this is the unique identifier for this bridge, consisting of bridge priority plus MAC address. This ID is the same for root and our bridge if the switch is the root switch.

zyMstpInfoInstanceInternalRootCost.name: zyMstpInfoInstanceInternalRootCost
zyMstpInfoInstanceInternalRootCost.description: This is the path cost from the root port in this MST instance to the regional root switch.

zyMstpInfoInstanceRootPort.name: zyMstpInfoInstanceRootPort
zyMstpInfoInstanceRootPort.description: This is the priority and number of the port on the switch through which this switch must communicate with the root of the MST instance.

zyMstpInfoInstanceTimeSinceTopologyChang.name: zyMstpInfoInstanceTimeSinceTopologyChange
zyMstpInfoInstanceTimeSinceTopologyChang.description: This is the time since the spanning tree was last reconfigured.

zyMstpInfoInstanceTopologyChangesCount.name: zyMstpInfoInstanceTopologyChangesCount
zyMstpInfoInstanceTopologyChangesCount.description: This is the number of times the spanning tree has been reconfigured.

zyxelMstpInfoInstancePortTable.name: zyxelMstpInfoInstancePortTable
zyxelMstpInfoInstancePortTable.description: The table contains MSTP instance port information.

zyxelMstpInfoInstancePortEntry.name: zyxelMstpInfoInstancePortEntry
zyxelMstpInfoInstancePortEntry.description: An entry contains MSTP instance port information.

zyMstpInfoInstancePortInstanceId.name: zyMstpInfoInstancePortInstanceId
zyMstpInfoInstancePortInstanceId.description: The number you want to use to identify this MST instance on the switch. 0 means CIST.

zyMstpInfoInstancePortPathCost.name: zyMstpInfoInstancePortPathCost
zyMstpInfoInstancePortPathCost.description: The cost of transmitting a frame on to a LAN through that port.

zyMstpInfoInstancePortState.name: zyMstpInfoInstancePortState
zyMstpInfoInstancePortState.description: STP assigns five port states to eliminate packet looping. A bridge port is not allowed to go directly from blocking state to forwarding state so as to eliminate transient loops.

zyMstpInfoInstancePortDesignatedRoot.name: zyMstpInfoInstancePortDesignatedRoot
zyMstpInfoInstancePortDesignatedRoot.description: The unique Bridge Identifier of the Bridge recorded as the Root in the Configuration BPDUs transmitted by the Designated Bridge for the segment to which the port is attached.

zyMstpInfoInstancePortDesignatedCost.name: zyMstpInfoInstancePortDesignatedCost
zyMstpInfoInstancePortDesignatedCost.description: The path cost of the Designated Port is connected to this port. This value is compared to the Root Path Cost field in received bridge PDUs.

zyMstpInfoInstancePortDesignatedBridge.name: zyMstpInfoInstancePortDesignatedBridge
zyMstpInfoInstancePortDesignatedBridge.description: The Bridge Identifier of the bridge that this port considers to be the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.

zyMstpInfoInstancePortDesignatedPort.name: zyMstpInfoInstancePortDesignatedPort
zyMstpInfoInstancePortDesignatedPort.description: The Port Identifier of the port on the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.

zyMstpNewRoot.name: zyMstpNewRoot
zyMstpNewRoot.description: The newRoot trap indicates that the sending agent has become the new root of the Spanning Tree; the trap is sent by a bridge soon after its election as the new root, e.g., upon expiration of the Topology Change Timer, immediately subsequent to its election. Implementation of this trap is optional.

zyMstpTopologyChange.name: zyMstpTopologyChange
zyMstpTopologyChange.description: A topologyChange is sent if the topology changed of MSTP has detected.
